# shadcn/ui

This project uses [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/) for all UI. Prefer existing primitives from `components/ui/` (or the path configured after init) instead of ad-hoc HTML styling or other component libraries.

## Setup

If shadcn is not initialized (no [components.json](mdc:components.json) at the project root, or the CLI says the project is not set up), run:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

## Adding components

If a needed primitive is missing, add it with the CLI, passing the component name from the shadcn docs. Example for the Button component:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

Replace `button` with the desired component (e.g. `card`, `dialog`, `input`). After adding, import from the project’s configured UI path and compose pages from these pieces.
